				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Multiphase extraction (MPE) is a physical remediation method used for treating contaminated soil and groundwater, particularly effective against halogenated volatile organic compounds (VOCs). It involves the use of a vacuum to remove a combination of impacted groundwater, free phase, and vapors from the subsurface. The extracted materials are then separated and treated above ground. MPE's efficiency depends on the optimization of operating conditions and can rehabilitate both saturated and unsaturated soil zones. It is often compared with traditional remediation methods to evaluate cost and performance.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">多相抽提（MPE）是一种物理修复方法，用于处理受污染的土壤和地下水，对卤代挥发性有机化合物（VOC）尤其有效。这种方法是利用真空将受影响的地下水、游离相和蒸汽从地表下分离出来。然后将提取的物质分离出来，并在地面上进行处理。MPE 的效率取决于操作条件的优化，可以修复饱和和非饱和土壤区域。它经常与传统的修复方法进行比较，以评估成本和性能。</common:generalComment>
